## SS 6. Subscribe to Newsletter (After Commenting)

Subscribe after commenting. Click triggers redirect to pledge page — subscription completes on first click. Navigate back immediately (skip interstitials).

**Step 1 — Click topmost Subscribe button on the post page:**

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1000));
    var btns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button'));
    // Check if already subscribed
    if (btns.some(b => /subscribed|following/i.test(b.innerText.trim()))) return { alreadySubscribed: true };
    var subBtns = btns.filter(b => b.innerText.trim() === 'Subscribe');
    if (subBtns.length === 0) return { error: 'no subscribe button' };
    // Click the topmost one (author's publication, not sidebar suggestions)
    var topBtn = subBtns.reduce((best, b) =>
      b.getBoundingClientRect().y < best.getBoundingClientRect().y ? b : best
    );
    topBtn.dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('click', { bubbles: true, cancelable: true }));
    return { clicked: true };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

**Step 2 — Navigate back to post (skip interstitials):**

The subscribe completes immediately on click. The redirect goes to a pledge page with 4 optional screens. Skip all of them by navigating back:

```
exec openclaw browser --browser-profile {{browser_profile}} navigate "{post_url}" 2>&1
```

Wait 2s, then verify no Subscribe button remains:

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000));
    var btns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button'));
    var hasSubscribe = btns.some(b => b.innerText.trim() === 'Subscribe');
    return { subscribed: !hasSubscribe };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

